<subSubSection id="7DE27D9CA14CC638E598D2755472D59D" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" type="notes">
<paragraph id="E4128DDC22A0C791100D001454799823" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="181A8E48EC2AABF85C2D978220E8F8FE" pageId="8" pageNumber="83">
Two specimens representing 
<taxonomicName id="5BFB23E36191C9A81E1B968825E82FC5" genus="T." lsidName="T. erythrina" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="erythrina">T. erythrina</taxonomicName>
clustered in a well-supported clade and were closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="F6050038EC93264B093F45AAB7083C98" genus="T." lsidName="T. samoensis" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="samoensis">T. samoensis</taxonomicName>
. These two species showed 97.6%-97.8% and 93.7%-96.0% sequence identities in the D1/D2 domain and ITS region, respectively. Basidia in 
<taxonomicName id="B33F06DDB6B1453AC987676923098BF1" genus="T." lsidName="T. erythrina" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="erythrina">T. erythrina</taxonomicName>
are larger than those of 
<taxonomicName id="F055015D36CF101175415D665481D5D9" genus="T." lsidName="T. samoensis" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="samoensis">T. samoensis</taxonomicName>
(12.0-18.0 
<normalizedToken id="4AD8CBF29604F906318CCD36A20E1D74" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="A31AC98BABD10B99D49BB55A6ECC1DCC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
13.0-19.0 
<normalizedToken id="2CBFDC2A8A18E0EED81B20F87B45A2B4" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName id="69FD99202395E80449E52FD819482466" genus="T." lsidName="T. erythrina" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="erythrina">T. erythrina</taxonomicName>
vs 12.0-18.0 
<normalizedToken id="9276449F3699A7F0E0B728D3BF8901FD" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="8F0DAF0765755D9BC12F56BD6B1732D1" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
8.0-12.0 
<normalizedToken id="0248FB2D8E343F71C8A1422DAE475A04" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName id="3E5139DA7EB39E0418A7D8624ED78D3A" genus="T." lsidName="T. samoensis" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="samoensis">T. samoensis</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="83D962C75D0F7302CB3F8246F60F6188" author="Chen, CJ" journalOrPublisher="Bibliotheca Mycologica" pageId="15" pageNumber="90" pagination="1 - 225" title="Morphological and molecular studies in the genus Tremella." volume="174" year="1998">Chen 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="01AE2DBAADE1C3F7FCDAF54E727F5B41" author="Malysheva, VF" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="16" pageNumber="91" pagination="40 - 70" title="The genus Tremella (Tremellales, Basidiomycota) in Russia with description of two new species and proposal of one nomenclatural combination." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.238.1.2" volume="238" year="2015">Malysheva et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
). Moreover, hyphidia are present and located in the hymenial structure and derived from the same generative hyphae with basidia in 
<taxonomicName id="9A99BBD217132CC878555505DDC47720" genus="T." lsidName="T. erythrina" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="erythrina">T. erythrina</taxonomicName>
, whereas hyphidia are lacking in 
<taxonomicName id="4267A336226293E24E0800D44AFE0825" genus="T." lsidName="T. samoensis" pageId="8" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="samoensis">T. samoensis</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="32725F94BA6D9BD3EDADB683A10C070A" author="Chen, CJ" journalOrPublisher="Bibliotheca Mycologica" pageId="15" pageNumber="90" pagination="1 - 225" title="Morphological and molecular studies in the genus Tremella." volume="174" year="1998">Chen 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="4AA67170EF4AE896F10E3586FE8CB21C" author="Malysheva, VF" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="16" pageNumber="91" pagination="40 - 70" title="The genus Tremella (Tremellales, Basidiomycota) in Russia with description of two new species and proposal of one nomenclatural combination." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.238.1.2" volume="238" year="2015">Malysheva et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
